<br>
I have played a shadowknight for two years, i have played many shadowknights and toyed around with stats and variouse things to get a knight i felt comfortable playing.<br>
<br>
I played Warriors origonally for a very long time until i was sick to death of them. So i do know the warrior vs knight comparison personally, i have hunted with warriors for a very long time and the same warriors so know about progression through the lv's.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> This relates to paladins, paladins are very simular to knights in may ways even though i hate to admit it</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
To set things straight here are some facts you should know:<br>
<br>
* Shadowknights can tank anything that does not need defensive fine, not many mobs 'requite' defensive, and you would be suprised how well knights can tank.<br>
   <br>
*Define high end - 'we' have had a shadowknight tank Va`Dyn and Zelnithack both very resently..... to some that is high end to others no....quite frankly as a warrior i dont want to tank statue of rallos zek....as a shadowknight i 'expect' to be able to fill in on raids if there is no warrior, and we do and that works fine. (better for an sk to tank than not dot he raid)<br>
<br>
*Pulling, who ever said sk's cant pull better than monks is on crack, shadowknights pull better than monks 90% of the time, you just need competent shadowknights and need to let them learn the lay of the land, pulling is mostly experience of the zone, class, game mecanics and a lot of good timing and tiny bit of luck. I have many good friends who play monks, and there is a time when they are bettter suited for the job, however sk's pull better than monks 90% of the time.. but in that 10% where monks shine ohh boy do they shine.<br>
<br>
*Lots of people still dont know how many methods there are of pulling.... Pulling in PoA when you jump the pegasus down to gorgolask island - sure safefall rocks and monks shine there, but that's one of a very small list of ways monks are better at pulling than shadowknights.<br>
     Added to the fact that shadowknights just make monks redundant at pulling in luclin (not been to VT yet so wont comment) luclin is just such a pointless place for monks to pull when competent shadowknights are there.<br>
<br>
*Hp Vs AC<br>
Shadowknights wont have many HP less than warriors, pre50 warriors have an easy time in gear so will have higher ac, once shadowknights get a good one handed wepon (first nice one is mace of shadowed soul) and a nice shield (25+ac) then they can outshine warriors on AC per equipment per lv very easily.<br>
      50+ it gets harder, warrior planar armor is so common vs shadowknight armor, warrior wepons drop in practically every zone vs shadowknights one or two, all the nice items that shadowknights get in the end game are in fact All/All or War/Pal/Shd/Clr/Brd and all the best shadowknight wepons are War/Pal/Shd or Shd/Pal.... But that is a HUGE gap between first planar and top of the game equipment.<br>
     Warrior <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Class</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> armor will always be better than Shadowknight <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Class</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Armour take for instance Plane of growth 28ac greaves (knight) and 36 ac greaves(war)<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pretty sure warrior is 36 quote me if i am wrong</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <br>
And that is why warriors 'have' the best armor, it's not until All/All armor comes into play that the knights catch back up, and HP wise Shadowknights if equall equiped gear wise will not be to far behind (the way it should be, shadowknights 'should' be a viable tank if no warrior shows up and paladins as well, we are not asking to be the best, just a 'useable' stand in.)<br>
<br>
*Damage, until knights get the 'high' end wepons warriors will always do more damage, shadowknights and paladins need two handed wepons to do comparable damage, even the lovely 20/20 one handed wepons soon become under par to the two handed drops.. with shield upgrades that helps damage with one handers by roughyl allowing knights to do bash into there 80's (can critical bash now) vs 15 on a average swing......big difference for bash damage. (have not tested but pal/sk epics should now do more bash damage also) But then this leads to a problem of getting a good shield, shields go from 19ac - 25ac -27ac -40ac...... the gap from a 25ac shield to higher is a BIG step, Chetari and Lodizal shields are there for the smaller end guilds and then things like Fearsome shield + are what you would be useing, even then Sword + Shield is situational, and two handed will always get you better damage for knights.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok Rant ended!!<br>
<br>
It really annoys me when people comment who know jack &amp;^%, my observing a knight and saying &quot;ooo he died to fast he cant tank&quot; is just rubish, we have many more gear configurations and spell configurations...... just the other night we had main tank die and i could 'not' get agro because i did not have one agro generating spell memorised, instead i had groupp atk/stamina buffs and variouse other spells including mid and self junk buffs, pulling spells and taps to heal myself through AOE, i was not expecting the main tank and secondary tank to plop down dead - Fortunatly we had somone who took initiative to grab agro fast, call it and saved the day, so what if he could not tank it as efficently, without him we would of wipedout almost certainly... But no one looks at the posative side, instead you are to busy class whining.<br>
<br>
And to all those, even some i know, who really dont understand the Paladin and Shadowknight classes - Learn abouth other classes more!!!!! There are plenty of Pro's Con's that so many of you dont even realise! heck some of the knights dont even realise it because they either never get a chance or lack the experience.... But it is out there if you know what to do, this is just player competence.<br>
